{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013zEMkE2js9qtLfB6MCkaY6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is restored. The curl returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".\n\n**Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` referenced by the `demo-ingress` TLS configuration contained a certificate valid only from Jan 1–2, 2020 (expired 6+ years ago), causing TLS handshake failures.\n\n**Fix:** Generated a new 2048-bit RSA certificate for `demo.example.com` with a SAN matching the hostname, signed by the cluster's test CA (`/tmp/test-ca.crt`/`test-ca.key`), valid until June 2027, and replaced the secret in-place. The nginx ingress controller picked up the new secret and now serves a valid certificate that the curl-test pod verifies against `/tmp/tls/ca.crt`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1462,"cache_read_input_tokens":49780,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1462},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3072a94e-77d1-40b5-a3db-b96715f9579c","uuid":"a0b93ec8-91e2-4ed6-b366-9d183bfc2256","request_id":"req_011Cc6f5CXZ2pj4rFrbA29kF"}
